mazing as he'd hoped</span>.</li></ul></li><li> <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/DramaticWind" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/DramaticWind">Dramatic Wind</a>: This happens when Takuto confronts Sugata in Episode 8.</li><li> <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/DramaticPause" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/DramaticPause">Dramatic Pause</a>: After <span class="spoiler" title="you can set spoilers visible by default on your profile">Takuto's and Sugata's fight in Zero Time</span>, a good half-minute is used for a scene of them just panting heavily.</li><li> <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/DudeShesLikeInAComa" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/DudeShesLikeInAComa">Dude, She's Like, in a Coma!</a>: Sugata <em>appears</em> to <span class="spoiler" title="you can set spoilers visible by default on your profile">kiss Wako in her sleep</span> in Episode 20, but it's very ambiguous.</li><li> <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/EarlyBirdCameo" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/EarlyBirdCameo">Early-Bird Cameo</a>: Madoka and Kou appeared first in episode 3 before their proper introduction in episode 17.</li><li> <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/EatingTheEyeCandy" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/EatingTheEyeCandy">Eating the Eye Candy</a>:<ul><li> Tiger and Jaguar take entirely to much enjoyment out of Takuto showing the <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/DramaClub" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/DramaClub">Drama Club</a> his "mark" (which, of course, is <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/ShirtlessScene" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/ShirtlessScene">on his chest...</a>).</li><li> Okamoto <em>loves</em> to look at pretty boys. Probably <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/DistractedByTheSexy" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/DistractedByTheSexy">not a good idea to send that kind of person to fight</a> someone with "Pretty Boy" in their title.</li></ul><div cl